<p>I am using Java collections BlockingQueue for data processing. The current code looks like</p>  <pre><code>while(true){     if(queue.size() &gt; 0)         handle(queue.take()) } </code></pre>  <p>Is there a way (in Java or other frameworks) where I can process it asynchronously, like, </p>  <pre><code>queue.setHandler(new Handler&lt;E&gt;()); </code></pre>  <p>somewhere down the class..</p>  <pre><code>class Handler implements IHandler&lt;E&gt;{     void handle(E e){         handle(e)     } } </code></pre>